    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. This example is powered by the high-revving S54B32 inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing. The powertrain is mated to a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-variable differential lock. Critical preventive maintenance has been addressed with surgical precision: the rear subframe has been reinforced, rod bearings replaced with VAC coated shells, and the VANOS system overhauled with Beisan components. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, exhibiting zero bushing deflection or fluid seepage. This is a mechanically transparent, turn-key specimen for the purist who demands peak atmospheric performance and structural integrity.",
